<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="539" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1593,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">
Type data: This species was described based on four females from 
<collectingCountry box="[899,954,1593,1619]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">Peru</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectionCode box="[995,1081,1593,1619]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">HNHM</collectionCode>
I found one female collected in “Yurimagua” and another one from “Tebas”. Both specimens must belong to the type series and are here designated 
<typeStatus box="[151,254,1665,1691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[312,466,1665,1691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">paralectotype</typeStatus>
, respectively. 
<typeStatus box="[628,740,1665,1691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">Lectotype</typeStatus>
with the following data label: [light greenish square without text]\ Yurimaguas [handwritten] Brasilia [printed]\ [black-rimmed] 685. 60. [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Typ. Mocs." authorityName="Typ. Mocs." box="[1176,1437,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulviventris">
<emphasis box="[1176,1302,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">fulviventris</emphasis>
Typ. Mocs.
</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]. 
<typeStatus box="[318,470,1737,1763]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
with the following data label: [purple square label without text]\ Tebas [handwritten] Brasilia [printed]\ [black-rimmed] 685. 60. [handwritten]. According to the accession book at 
<collectionCode box="[1200,1286,1773,1799]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">HNHM</collectionCode>
the 
<typeStatus box="[1334,1437,1773,1799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[198,349,1809,1835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">paralectotype</typeStatus>
were purchased from insect dealer Otto Staudinger in 1884. The current condition and depository of the remaining type specimens, now 
<typeStatus box="[584,749,1845,1871]" pageId="5" pageNumber="539">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
, is unknown.
</paragraph>
